{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0d27b4a7-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1087–4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1087–4"},"text":"§ 1087–4.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Discrimination in secondary markets prohibited","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Student Loan Marketing Association (and, if the Association is privatized under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1087–3"},"text":"section 1087–3 of this title","children":[],"tail":", any successor entity functioning as a secondary market for loans under this part, including the Holding Company described in such section) shall not engage directly or indirectly in any pattern or practice that results in a denial of a borrower’s access to loans under this part because of the borrower’s race, sex, color, religion, national origin, age, disability status, income, attendance at a particular eligible institution, length of the borrower’s educational program, or the borrower’s academic year at an eligible institution."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0d27b4a8-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/329/tIV/s440A"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–329, title IV, § 440A","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/208/dA/tI/s101/e/tVI/s604"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–208, div. A, title I, § 101(e) [title VI, § 604]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3009-233"},"text":"110 Stat. 3009–233","children":[],"tail":", 3009–293.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id0d27b4a9-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"e